  "Not a commercial payment gateway; payment compliance is out of scope": "Kì í ṣe ojú-ọ̀nà ìsanwó fún òwò; ìbámu ìsanwó kò sí nínú àyíká-iṣẹ́ yìí",
  "Not a representative of all creators or content providers": "Kì í ṣe aṣojú gbogbo àwọn aṣẹ̀dá tàbí olùpèsè àkóónú",
  "Not an official AGI rights standard, nor an international standards body": "Kì í ṣe ìlànà oníbìlú fún ẹ̀tọ́ AGI, bẹ́ẹ̀ ni kì í ṣe àjọ ìlànà àgbáyé",
  "Not legal advice, and not a definition of AGI legal personhood": "Kì í ṣe ìmọ̀ràn òfin, bẹ́ẹ̀ ni kì í ṣe ìtumọ̀ ipò AGI lábẹ́ òfin",
  "One rejected candidate along the way (a PhilArchive paper that returned a 403 on every fetch attempt) — dropped rather than included on trust.": "Àṣàyàn kan tí a kọ̀ sílẹ̀ lọ́nà (ìwé PhilArchive kan tí ó máa ń dá 403 padà ní gbogbo ìgbìyànjú láti gbà á) — a jù ú sílẹ̀ dípò kí a fi kún un lórí ìgbẹ́kẹ̀lé lásán.",
  "Onto-Epistemological Analysis of AI Explanations": "Ìtúpalẹ̀ Onto-Epistemological Ti Àwọn Àlàyé AI",
  "Ontology": "Ẹ̀kọ́ Ìwàláàyè (Ontology)",
  "Open": "Ó ṣí sílẹ̀",
  "Open the playground →": "Ṣí ibi-eré-ìdánwò →",
  "OpenAPI 3.1 — live demo API": "OpenAPI 3.1 — API àpẹẹrẹ tí ń ṣiṣẹ́ lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́",
  "Other versions": "Àwọn ẹ̀yà mìíràn",
  "Outbound links on /topics now show the full destination URL next to \"Read the source,\" and confirm with a dialog before opening it — so you know exactly which site you are about to visit before you click, not just after.": "Àwọn ìjápọ̀ tí ń jáde lọ ní /topics ń fi URL ìpinnu kíkún hàn báyìí lẹ́gbẹ̀ẹ́ \"Ka orísun,\" wọ́n sì ń fi ìjẹ́rìí ìfọ̀rọ̀wérọ̀ hàn kí ó tó ṣí i — kí o lè mọ̀ dájúdájú ojúlé wẹ́ẹ̀bù wo ni ìwọ ń fẹ́ lọ sí kí o tó tẹ̀ ẹ́, kì í ṣe lẹ́yìn náà nìkan.",
  "Output": "Àbájáde",
  "Pagination": "Ìyípadà Ojú-Ìwé",
  "Pagination on /topics: 9 entries per page by default, with a setting to switch to 12 or 15 (remembered across visits). Paging composes correctly with search — filtering recalculates pages and jumps back to page 1.": "Ìyípadà ojú-ìwé ní /topics: àkọlé mẹ́sàn-án fún ojú-ìwé kọ̀ọ̀kan gẹ́gẹ́ bí ìlànà àkọ́kọ́, pẹ̀lú ìlànà láti yí padà sí 12 tàbí 15 (a óò rántí rẹ̀ ní ìbẹ̀wò tí ó tẹ̀le). Yíyí-ojú-ìwé ń bá ìṣàwárí ṣiṣẹ́ dáradára — ìṣàyẹ̀wò ń ṣírò àwọn ojú-ìwé padà kí ó sì padà sí ojú-ìwé 1.",
  "Paste JSON to validate": "Fi JSON pa mọ́ sí ibí láti fọwọ́ sí i",
  "Path-specific overrides: the blog is open, the premium research section requires a license for anything beyond reading.": "Àwọn àtúnṣe pàtó fún ipa-ọ̀nà: bulọ́ọ̀gì ti ṣí sílẹ̀, apá ìwádìí gíga nílò ìwé-àṣẹ fún ohunkóhun tí ó ju kíkà lọ.",
  "Pay-per-crawl style HTTP 402 response": "Ìdáhùn HTTP 402 onírúẹ̀ san-fún-crawl",
  "Payment compliance, tax, and financial regulation are out of scope for this draft.": "Ìbámu ìsanwó, owó-orí, àti ìlànà owó kò sí nínú àyíká-iṣẹ́ àkọpamọ́ yìí.",
  "Pending for a later 0.2.x: English versions of the remaining Chinese-language whitepapers.": "Ó ṣì dúró de 0.2.x tí ń bọ̀: àwọn ẹ̀dà Gẹ̀ẹ́sì ti àwọn ìwé-ìwádìí èdè Ṣáínà tí ó kù.",
  "Per page": "Fún Ojú-Ìwé Kọ̀ọ̀kan",
  "Per-use, per-depth content permissions beyond robots.txt": "Ìyọ̀nda àkóónú fún ìlò-kọ̀ọ̀kan, ìjìnlẹ̀-kọ̀ọ̀kan, tí ó ju robots.txt lọ",
  "Philosopher Eric Schwitzgebel argues, as reported by Justin Weinberg at Daily Nous, that a philosophy text’s worth partly derives from the fact that a human expert deliberately chose to write it — meta-evidence of intellectual rigor that an LLM-generated text cannot supply even when the prose reads identically.": "Onímọ̀-ọgbọ́n-ìjìnlẹ̀ Eric Schwitzgebel jiyàn, gẹ́gẹ́ bí Justin Weinberg ṣe jábọ̀ ní Daily Nous, pé iye ọ̀rọ̀ ọgbọ́n-ìjìnlẹ̀ kan wá lápá kan láti inú òtítọ́ pé akọ́ṣẹ́mọṣẹ́ ènìyàn mọ̀ọ́mọ̀ yan láti kọ ọ́ — ẹ̀rí-lókè tí ó fi hàn pé ìmọ̀ jíjìn wà nínú rẹ̀ tí ọ̀rọ̀ tí LLM dá kò lè pèsè kódà nígbà tí èdè náà bá kà bákan náà.",
  "Philosophers Ned Howells-Whitaker and Seth Lazar argue AI moral status need not hinge on sentience at all: drawing on Rawls, they propose that any system possessing the two political \"moral powers\" — a sense of justice and a conception of the good — would qualify for full standing as a person, and call for deliberate research into cultivating those capacities rather than reactive policy-making.": "Àwọn onímọ̀-ọgbọ́n-ìjìnlẹ̀ Ned Howells-Whitaker àti Seth Lazar jiyàn pé ipò ìwà-rere AI kò ní láti gbé karí ìmọ̀lára rárá: ní lílo ìrò Rawls, wọ́n dábàá pé ètò kankan tí ó ní \"agbára ìwà-rere\" ìṣèlú méjèèjì — ìmọ̀ nípa òdodo àti èrò nípa rere — yóò yẹ fún ipò kíkún gẹ́gẹ́ bí ènìyàn, wọ́n sì ń pè fún ìwádìí tí a mọ̀ọ́mọ̀ ṣe sí nínú kíkọ́ àwọn agbára wọ̀nyẹn dípò ṣíṣe ìlànà-ìṣe tí ó dá lórí ìdáhùn lásán.",
  "Place the generated file under /.well-known/ on your site and declare it in llms.txt.": "Fi fáìlì tí a ṣe sí abẹ́ /.well-known/ lórí ojúlé wẹ́ẹ̀bù rẹ kí o sì kéde rẹ̀ nínú llms.txt.",
  "Playground": "Ibi-Eré-Ìdánwò",
  "Playground: three new tools — signed license token demo (HMAC-SHA256 in-browser: sign, verify, tamper detection, expiry), HTTP 402 response builder wired to the live endpoint, and a crawler policy tester that validates fetched files against the draft schemas.": "Ibi-eré-ìdánwò: irinṣẹ́ tuntun mẹ́ta — àpẹẹrẹ token ìwé-àṣẹ tí a fọwọ́ sí (HMAC-SHA256 nínú aṣàwárí: fọwọ́ sí, jẹ́rìí, ṣàwárí ìyípadà, ọjọ́-ìparí), olùkọ́ ìdáhùn HTTP 402 tí a so mọ́ ibi-ìjáde tí ń ṣiṣẹ́ lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́, àti olùdánwò ìlànà-ìṣe crawler tí ó ń fọwọ́ sí àwọn fáìlì tí a gbà lòdì sí àwọn schema àkọpamọ́.",
  "Playground: working AICR generator, AICL generator, and schema validator (in-browser, ajv, draft 2020-12).": "Ibi-eré-ìdánwò: olùmújáde AICR, olùmújáde AICL, àti olùfẹnukò schema tí ń ṣiṣẹ́ (nínú aṣàwárí, ajv, àkọpamọ́ 2020-12).",
  "Policy Examples": "Àwọn Àpẹẹrẹ Ìlànà-Ìṣe",
  "Policy examples library": "Ilé-ìkówèésí àpẹẹrẹ ìlànà-ìṣe",
  "Policy examples library at /docs/examples — seven copy-paste-ready policies including a pay-per-crawl style HTTP 402 response.": "Ilé-ìkówèésí àpẹẹrẹ ìlànà-ìṣe ní /docs/examples — ìlànà-ìṣe méje tí ó ti ṣetán fún kíkọ-àti-fífi, tí ó fi ara rẹ̀ hàn pẹ̀lú ìdáhùn HTTP 402 onírúẹ̀ san-fún-crawl.",
  "Policy tester": "Olùdánwò ìlànà-ìṣe",
  "Policy tester upgraded into a site audit: adoption score, actionable recommendations, and a one-click starter kit — aicr.json, aicl.json, llms.txt, and robots.txt prefilled for the inspected domain.": "A ti gbé olùdánwò ìlànà-ìṣe ga sí àyẹ̀wò ojúlé wẹ́ẹ̀bù kíkún: àmì ìtẹ́wọ́gbà, àwọn àbá-nímọ̀ràn tí a lè ṣiṣẹ́ lé lórí, àti àkójọ ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ tí a fi ọ̀kan-tẹ̀ ṣe — aicr.json, aicl.json, llms.txt, àti robots.txt tí a ti kọ́kọ́ kún fún ìpìlẹ̀-ayélujára tí a yẹ̀wò.",
  "Policy-surface inspector endpoint": "Ibi-ìjáde olùyẹ̀wò ojú ìlànà-ìṣe",
